# File Upload: Drag-and-Drop Zone

Whenever the page has an `<input type="file">` for selecting files, provide a **dedicated drag-and-drop area** with a modern look, instead of only a plain "בחירת קובץ" button.

## Requirements

- A visible **drop zone** (e.g. dashed border, rounded corners, padding) that accepts drag-and-drop.
- **Click-to-browse**: clicking the zone triggers the file input (input hidden or overlayed with `opacity: 0` / `position: absolute`).
- **Feedback**: on `dragover` / `dragenter` add a class (e.g. `drag-over`) to change background/border; remove on `dragleave` and `drop`.
- **Accessibility**: keep the native `<input type="file">` in the DOM; associate a label or use `aria-label` on the zone so screen readers understand it.
- **RTL**: text like "גרור קובץ לכאן או לחץ לבחירה" (or similar) in Hebrew.

## Markup pattern

```html
<label class="file-drop-zone" id="file_drop_zone">
    <input type="file" name="csv_file" accept=".csv" class="file-drop-input" id="file_input">
    <span class="file-drop-text">גרור קובץ לכאן או לחץ לבחירה</span>
    <span class="file-drop-hint">CSV עד 5MB</span>
</label>
```

- Zone: `class="file-drop-zone"` (or `file-upload-zone`).
- Input: hidden visually (`width: 0; height: 0; opacity: 0; position: absolute`) or use a separate `<input>` and trigger `.click()` from the zone’s click handler.
- Optional: show selected file name after choice via JS.

## Styling (modern)

- Dashed border (e.g. `2px dashed #d1d5db`), `border-radius: 12px`, padding `1.5rem`, background `#f9fafb`.
- Hover: `border-color: #9ca3af`, background `#f3f4f6`.
- `.drag-over`: border primary color (e.g. `#4f46e5`), background tint (e.g. `#eef2ff`).
- Centered text and optional icon (e.g. Lucide `upload`).

## Do not

- Rely only on a small "בחירת קובץ" button with no drop zone.
- Use a native file input as the only visible control when space allows for a full drop area.
